Third-party software.

The portable core of this module depends on the Go standard library alone.
Key derivation uses crypto/hkdf, which entered the standard library in Go
1.24; no third-party module is required to build, test, or embed the core.

The fido provider, which reaches real hardware and builds only on Windows,
depends on one module, obtained as a Go module and not redistributed as part
of this source tree.  Its license governs its own code:

  BSD 3-Clause License
    golang.org/x/sys

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Embedded data.

The files under roots/ are attestation trust anchors published by Yubico.
They are data, not code: certificates, distributed so this module can verify
that an enrolling security key is genuine hardware.  Their provenance is
recorded in the headers of the PEM files themselves.  They are not covered by
this module's license and confer no endorsement by their issuer.
